Patch Set 1:

Could that be an issue when upgrading files in etc/?

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2

Hi Ying,

I'm sorry but I've to block this. This change could break clouds during upgrades from a version to another. I believe we'll have to live with the inconsistency as far as this metadefs go. 

(Unless I'm missing something, since I'm not a metadefs expert)

Patch Set 1:

Flavio Percoco, thanks for checking this patch. If we don't fix the inconsistency, the nova feature for setting topology constraints won't be utilized. https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/virt/hardware.py#L278. I think even if we don't fix it as a defect, we should still make the changes as a new feature to utilize what nova is offering.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Looking the Nova code you pointed out this seems to be bug in Nova side looking for wrong keys introduced in 36d37a67

Patch Set 1:

Erno Kuvaja, https://github.com/openstack/nova/commit/36d37a670ea6c82aa37318898c43bb657e47128c didn't change the name. Anyway, I think this inconsistency can be fixed in either glance or nova. If you don't think glance can take this change, I can open a defect in nova.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

I don't know much about Glance metadata, but I think Ying Zuo has a point here. The actual Nova code uses the underscore-separated version of these names[1], meaning the versions defined here are invalid. Either Nova needs to change the metadata it checks for (which it won't, as the name is valid), or Glance needs to make a correct request.

Also, if I'm reading this correctly then this won't do anything to upgrades as the metadata isn't currently being picked up by Nova.

Correct me if I'm wrong :)

Patch Set 1:

[1] https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/f396826/nova/virt/hardware.py#L313

Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

Flavio and Erno, can you guys please follow up with your comments based on explanations?

I think it's a okay change.

Since, we're in RC phase we will not be able to accommodate this change.

It has an upgrade impact and if it is critical we can consider it for rc2. Please show up at the glance meeting on thursday (soon) to make the case.

https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/glance-team-meeting-agenda
